          <p class="lead">Need a new <strong>furnace installation in Lake Charles</strong>? Latour's HVAC installs high-efficiency gas and electric furnaces designed for reliable heating during Louisiana winters. We help you choose the right furnace for your home, ensure proper sizing, and provide expert installation backed by manufacturer warranties.</p>

          <p>While heat pumps are popular in our mild climate, many Lake Charles homeowners prefer the warmth of a gas furnace. Gas furnaces deliver hotter air (110-140°F) compared to heat pumps (85-95°F), which some people find more comfortable during cold snaps.</p>

          <h2>Types of Furnaces We Install</h2>

          <h3>Gas Furnaces</h3>
          <p>The most popular choice for Lake Charles homes with natural gas service. Modern gas furnaces achieve efficiency ratings of 80-98% AFUE (Annual Fuel Utilization Efficiency).</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Single-Stage:</strong> Basic operation, lower cost, reliable performance</li>
            <li><strong>Two-Stage:</strong> Runs at low capacity most of the time for better comfort and efficiency</li>
            <li><strong>Variable-Speed/Modulating:</strong> Precise temperature control, highest efficiency, quietest operation</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Electric Furnaces</h3>
          <p>A good option for homes without gas service. Electric furnaces have lower installation costs but higher operating costs than gas.</p>

          <h3>Dual Fuel Systems</h3>
          <p>Combines a heat pump with a gas furnace backup. The heat pump handles mild weather efficiently, while the furnace provides powerful heating during the coldest days.</p>

